<Legal title="Privacy Policy" updated="12 June 2026">
  <p>
    Doghouse Media ("we", "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This
    policy explains what personal data we collect, how we use it, and your rights
    under the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the Irish Data
    Protection Act 2018. We are the data controller for the information described
    here.
  </p>

  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Enquiry details</strong> — your name, email, company, phone number,
      and the project information you submit through our contact form.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Usage data</strong> — basic, anonymised information about how the
      site is used, where analytics are enabled.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How we use your data</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To respond to your enquiry and provide a quote or proposal.</li>
    <li>To deliver and manage projects you engage us for.</li>
    <li>To meet our legal and accounting obligations.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Our lawful bases for processing are your consent, the performance of a
    contract, and our legitimate interest in running our business.
  </p>

  <h2>Sharing your data</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell your personal data. We only share it with trusted service
    providers who help us operate — for example email and hosting providers — and
    only to the extent necessary. These providers are bound by their own data
    protection obligations.
  </p>

  <h2>Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep enquiry and project data only for as long as needed for the purposes
    above, or as required by law (for example, financial records are retained for
    six years).
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    You have the right to access, correct, or erase your personal data, to
    restrict or object to its processing, and to data portability. To exercise
    any of these rights, email
    <a href="mailto:hello@doghousemedia.ie">hello@doghousemedia.ie</a>. You also
    have the right to lodge a complaint with the Irish Data Protection Commission
    (<a href="https://www.dataprotection.ie" target="_blank" rel="noopener">dataprotection.ie</a>).
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    For details on how we use cookies, see our
    <a href="/cookie-policy/">Cookie Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Doghouse Media, 13 Adelaide Rd, Dublin 2, D02 P950, Ireland —
    <a href="mailto:hello@doghousemedia.ie">hello@doghousemedia.ie</a>.
  </p>
</Legal>
